article.headline: Arkansas 75, Nicholls State 40
article.story:
HOT SPRINGS, Ark. (AP) -- Kristin Moore scored 14 points and
pulled down 14 rebounds to help Arkansas gain a 75-40 win Thursday
night over Nicholls State.

The Lady Razorbacks (5-4) had more than doubled the visitors'
score at halftime, 33-16, and cruised to the victory after
intermission.

Katherine Plummer was the only player for Nicholls State (1-6)
to score in double figures, with 13 points.

Arkansas' Dominique Washington scored 15 to lead all scores,
while Leslie Howard came off the bench to get 14 points.
